# Docker.io vs Docker-ce
You have two options to install Docker on Debian, straight answer: what differs is the build process, and mostly, the way dependencies are handled
- from docker.com (this package is named docker-ce), go dependecies. docker-ce you can fetch the source code with git (it includes the packaging files)
- from the Debian repositories (this package is named docker.io), apt dependencies.

#NOTE: 'docker-compose' cli app indicate that is V1 and 'docker compose' indicate V2, see: cheat docker-compose

# Start docker daemon
docker -d

# create project from init
docker init

#build
docker build .
docker build --rm . # delete intermidate containers
docker build --rm -f Dockerfile -t <image_name_given> .

